             <li>Study the Chapter guides on ITILstudy.com: Explain the goals, objectives, scope and basic concepts of core ITIL processes & functions and other syllabus areas of ITIL.</li>
             <li>Complete the exercises for each chapter which include:
              <ol type="a"><br/>
               <li>Chapter Tests: The Chapter Tests assess the delegate's degree of understanding of the respective chapter content.</li>
               <li>Fill in the blanks: Fill in the blanks help the delegates remember the key terms with regards to each chapter and ensure the re-enforcement of important terms to remember.</li>
              </ol>
             </li>
             <li>Take two full length sample tests from APMG: To get a feel of the actual ITIL Foundation exam, take the APMG's full length sample tests as part of our online courses and assess your responses with the provided answers to the same.</li>
             <li>Take ITILstudy Mock Tests: To further strengthen your preparation and improve on your shortcomings before you attempt the exam.</li>
             <li>Take the ITIL Foundation exam: You are ready to take the ITIL Foundation Certification Exam. All you need to do is contact APMG to book the Foundation exam at your preferred location.</li>

